@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "BBBubbles" where you want 
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any white bubble in the 7 by 7 spaces board,
this will change it to its assigned colour. If one or more coloured
bubbles of the same size are next to the clicked bubble, they will
blow up and you will get points according to the number of blown up
bubbles... note that you get much more points if they are all of
the same colour. See the following table:

 Blown up bubbles   Different colours   Same colour
    2 bubbles            1 point          10 points
    3 bubbles            2 points         40 points
    4 bubbles            4 points        160 points
    5 bubbles            8 points        640 points

  As bubbles are blown up, they are removed fromn the board and are
then replaced by new white bubbles.

  Pay attention to the 'Bubble-O-Meter', indicated by a white
bubble at the right of the game board. If that bubble decrease in
size, that means that there are few neighbouring bubbles of the
same size... if it blows up, the game is over.

  You can quit the game anytime by pressing on the 'Esc' key on the
keyboard.

  Have fun!

